OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F379A1781183479
OL,3,CSix fire engines called to Grade II
OL,4,Cfactory blaze as police close roads
OL,6,FOne resident, Sally Moore, said: "This
OL,7,Fmorning when we woke up, we saw the
OL,8,Ffire at the roof of the old factory
OL,9,Ffrom our house.
OL,11,F"Thankfully, the fire service turned
OL,12,Fup quickly and we've not had to leave
OL,13,Four house.J"The building is already
OL,14,Fdeteriorating so much, the fire must
OL,15,Fhave done a lot of damage to it."
OL,17,FAnother resident added: "I parked my
OL,18,Fcar on Heanor Road last night and now
OL,19,Fcan't get to it so I'll be missing
OL,20,Fwork. Most importantly it looks like
OL,21,Feveryone is safe though."
